        <h1>
          Article 33: Power of Parliament to modify the rights conferred by this
          Part in their application to Forces, etc.
        </h1>
        <p>
          * Article 33 of the Indian Constitution allows the Parliament to
          modify or restrict fundamental rights for members of the armed forces,
          police forces, and other similar organizations.
        </p>
        <p>
          *Article 33 allows the Parliament to make laws that can limit or
          modify fundamental rights for members of the armed forces, police, and
          other similar groups. This is done to ensure discipline and efficiency
          in these organizations.
        </p>
        <p>
          * The article recognizes that these forces need specific rules and
          regulations that may require restrictions on certain fundamental
          rights to maintain discipline and effective functioning.
        </p>
        <p>
          * In simple terms, Article 33 lets the government limit fundamental
          rights for military and police personnel to ensure they can perform
          their duties effectively and maintain discipline.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ar20">
