          Article 34: Restriction on rights conferred by this Part while martial
          law is in force in any area
        </h1>
        <p>
          * Article 34 of the Indian Constitution deals with the suspension of
          fundamental rights during the period of martial law and the protection
          of actions taken under such laws.
        </p>
        <p>
          * Article 34 allows the suspension of certain fundamental rights
          during a period of martial law (when the military takes over control
          due to emergencies or unrest). This ensures that the armed forces can
          operate effectively under such conditions.
        </p>
        <p>
          * It provides protection to actions taken by authorities under martial
          law. This means that the actions of the military or authorities during
          this period cannot be challenged in court on the grounds that they
          violate fundamental rights.
        </p>
        <p>
          * In simple terms, Article 34 allows for the suspension of certain
          fundamental rights and shields actions taken under martial law from
          being challenged in court.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="seccontainer">
